<a href="page_3.htm"><img border="0" src="next.gif" width="26" height="26"></a></p>
<p align="center"><font size="7">Why SOAP?</font></p>
<ul>
  <li>
  <h2><span style="font-weight: 400"><font size="6">It is important for application development to allow 
  Internet communication between programs.</font></span></h2>
  </li>
  <li>
  <h2><span style="font-weight: 400"><font size="6">RPC represents a compatibility and security problem; 
  firewalls and proxy servers will normally block this kind of traffic.</font></span></h2>
  </li>
  <li>
  <h2><span style="font-weight: 400"><font size="6">A better way to communicate between applications is over 
  HTTP, because HTTP is supported by all Internet browsers and servers. SOAP was 
  created to accomplish this.</font></span></h2>
  </li>
  <li>
  <h2><span style="font-weight: 400"><font size="6">SOAP is a key element of Microsoft's .NET architecture for 
  future Internet application development</font></span></h2>
  </li>
</ul>

</body>

